Attendees place offerings Sunday in remembrance of the ancestors who perished through the Middle Passage during the slave trade. The South Miami-Dade NAACP presented the "Year of the Return: Remembering 400 Years of Africans in America" with prayers, healing circle, libations, and songs at the historic Virginia Key Beach Park in Florida, the once segregated beach for African-Americans. Photo: VCGÂ  
